heat oven to 180C
line 2 muffin trays with paper mufin casses. 
In a large bowl beat 2 medium eggs lightly  for 1 min.
Add 125ml vegetable oil and 250ml milk and beat until just combined. 
then add 250g golden caster sugar and whisk until you have a smooth batter.
Sift in 400g flour and 1 tsp salt, then mix until just smooth.( Be careful not to over-mix the batter as this will make the muffins tough.)
Stir in 100g chocolate chips or dried fruit if using.
Fill muffin cases two-thirds full and bake for 20-25 mins, until risen.
Leave the muffins in the tin to cool for a few mins and transfer to a wire rack to cool completely.
Serve when is completely cool 